1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a natural language processing task of identifying relevant sentences for claim verification. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed algorithm is trainable with gradient-based methods. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a submodular optimization approach for subset selection. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with selecting informative sentences from a larger set. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the proposed method could potentially be applied to image or video subset selection tasks.
